reviewText: I love this show and all of the characters in it. I found this for a real good price and I am going to look for more deals like this to add to my collection. Thank u.
Title: Friends: The Complete Fifth and Sixth Seasons

reviewText: I bought this for my girlfriend.  She watched Friends on TV originally and wanted to watch it again in order.  So we have slowly been collecting the seasons.  I checked around and I think the 2 season combo is the way to go.  I paid $19.99 and it qualified for free super saver shipping.  That is only $10.00 a season for a brand new copy.  It seemed the individual seasons cost about $15 new.  Used copys can be a little bit cheaper, but then you never really know what the condition will be.It is a funny show too.  If you haven't watched it before and you are looking for a chuckle, I would check it out.
summary: Purchased as a gift, great deal
Title: Friends: The Complete Fifth and Sixth Seasons

reviewText: one of my favorite shows and these seasons are awesome. I watch it with my girlfriend all the time and we can't get enough.buy this.....now!
Title: Friends: The Complete Fifth and Sixth Seasons

reviewText: Bought this as a package bargain price deal.  I love Friends, so I added to my set for a reasonable price.  Chandler and Monica are married and Rachel and Ross "accidently" tie the knot too.  Lots of fun and some pain, as real life friends go through. Highly recommend if you are a Friends fan like me.
Title: Friends: The Complete Fifth and Sixth Seasons

reviewText: This is a great series for anyone that loves a quick laugh. The show is funny, climactic at points and dramatic. It plays on several stereotypes and satirizes several aspects of society. My only recommendation? Start with season 1!
Title: Friends: The Complete Fifth and Sixth Seasons

reviewText: This show is about friends always trying to keep each others friendships going without hurting anyone's feeling's and always messing it up in a funny way. Constantly making me laugh.
Title: Friends: The Complete Fifth and Sixth Seasons

reviewText: I bought the entire series throughout this year and have been watching it most of the time. While I prefer the earlier seasons episodes, seasons 1-7, there were enough funny episodes in the 8- 10 seasons to warrant purchasing them all.
Title: Friends: The Complete Fifth and Sixth Seasons

reviewText: Hands down, this is one of the best shows EVER. I can watch it over and over, it never gets old!
Title: Friends: The Complete Fifth and Sixth Seasons

reviewText: Don't purchase the Blu-Ray version till they do it right like this complete collection.  The picture may not be widescreen but it is what you seen on TV plus little extra.  The Blu-ray version is just a cropped version of this with shorter episodes.  Glad I didn't wait to long and miss out on these.
Title: Friends: The Complete Fifth and Sixth Seasons

reviewText: These two seasons in one arrived in my mailbox very quickly and in perfect shape.  Now I have something to watch this cold and dreary winter~
Title: Friends: The Complete Fifth and Sixth Seasons

reviewText: I was so looking forward to receiving the Fifth & Sixth Seasons as I hadn't seen all of Friends ever.  The second disc (I think) of the Fifth Season has audio issues and I can't hear it.  Season Six has issues with the voice not matching the mouths as the actors are speaking and it is awful to watch.  How do you make this right for me since I have paid my money?  If there is no way, I will never purchase another item from Amazon.
Title: Friends: The Complete Fifth and Sixth Seasons

reviewText: What I like about the packaging is that all episodes for the season are squished into 4 discs and all 4 discs are in one case.  Nice and tidy and convenient for storage and travel.
summary: Seasons 5 and 6 just as funny as the first.
Title: Friends: The Complete Fifth and Sixth Seasons

reviewText: Bought this as a gift for my wife who loves friends. Would recommend this to any Friends fans out there.
Title: Friends: The Complete Fifth and Sixth Seasons

reviewText: How can a show like this stay so fresh and simple?  Great writing, editing, producing, and casting!  I guess anyone who appreciates the efforts of what Hollywood does can see that a show, like Friends, marks our very souls and makes a difference in our lives.
